<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,1389,1774]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1677,1702]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Remarks.</emphasis>
We recognized this species from 
<bibRefCitation author="Cerretti &amp; Tschorsnig" box="[689,1017,1677,1702]" firstAuthor="Cerretti" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="271 - 286" refId="ref32552" refString="Cerretti, P. &amp; Tschorsnig, H. - P. (2012) Three new species of Estheria Robineau-Desvoidy (Diptera: Tachinidae) from the Mediterranean, with a key to the European and Mediterranean species of the genus. Stuttgarter Beitrage zur Naturkunde A, Neue Serie, 5, 271 - 286." type="journal article" year="2012">Cerretti &amp; Tschorsnig (2012)</bibRefCitation>
. It is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Meigen)" authorityName="Meigen" baseAuthorityName="Meigen" baseAuthorityYear="1826" box="[1189,1389,1677,1702]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Estheria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="picta">
<emphasis box="[1189,1276,1678,1701]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">E. picta</emphasis>
(Meigen)
</taxonomicName>
, but differs from the latter in having narrower frons, first flagellomere light brown to black, and postpronotum entirely black.
</paragraph>
